The query language allows users to retrieve information from the data base by posing queries in response to the systems prompt. For example, to find all computer programmers one can say
;;; Query input: (job ?x (computer programmer))
// Query input: job(x, list("computer", "programmer"));

The system will respond with the following items:
;;; Query results: (job (Hacker Alyssa P) (computer programmer)) (job (Fect Cy D) (computer programmer))
// Query results: job(list("Hacker", "Alyssa", "P"), list("computer", "programmer")) job(list("Fect", "Cy", "D"), list("computer", "programmer"))

